    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_442523">Some got sent out early by mistake.<br />
<br />
And of course, all 3 books are available as a torrent with OEF quality already. Although those are leaked documents from printers - so they have the color test patterns and stuff on each page. But still, it's an OEF and not a scan.<br />
<br />
While WotC tried to shut down the torrents fast, it multiplied faster than rabbits and thus should still be available on multiple sites.<br />
<br />
A friend of mine and me, we are both GMs here in local groups, have both preordered all 3 books... will probably not get them until end of June since they are ordered from the USA.<br />
<br />
So I had a look at the books, and while it's absolutely not what I expected for D&amp;D 4th, it's interesting and I'm looking forward to playing it. Although I hesitate to call it D&amp;D 4th, because well.. there basically is NOTHING left of what makes D&amp;D... but it seems to be a solid system that should play well.<br />
<br />
Edit: Anyhow, I don't plan of cancelling my orders - that's for sure <img src="images/smilies/emote_smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smile" class="inlineimg" /> I'm a collector..</div>
