    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_443969">Fourth Edition does not feel like d&amp;d. Much more like wow meets diablo 2. Roles are too well defined for my tastes, at least so far. I dislike how often everyone can do cool stuff. Every action you do should not have a special name (unless you do so for flavor for your character) -- it feels a little too forced, and makes me feel like my character isn't as unique. <br />
However, I do like some aspects of it, like how they've streamlined the system for ac and saves, and I like the set of gods much better.<br />
I also like the idea of being unaligned, but i don't like getting rid of lawful evil or chaotic good. <br />
It feels a lot more shallow now, overall. Which does promote (sometimes) faster gameplay, and easier character builds, but it sacrifices dedication to a character.<br />
<br />
-Smurf</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
