</div>I agree with this part, but not so much because of the system - I've read all the books (spent around $1500 to buy what was available this summer) and honestly liked what they did with things. I also wasn't a fan of 3E, at least by the time 3.5 came out. It just got too bloated with too many &quot;I can make this prestige class section more powerful than the last!&quot; books.<br />
<br />
On the other hand, I HATE the direction they've taken with 4th in making the books all crunch and no fluff. I can kinda understand doing it with the baseline books, but the setting books are such a joke too. Their &quot;we don't want to develop the FR in the FR book, that's what the novels are for!&quot; excuse is ********.</div>
